HPE Aruba Networking Central (Classic Ce.name: HPE Aruba Networking Central (Classic Central)
HPE Aruba Networking Central (Classic Ce.description:
HPE Aruba Networking Central is a unified cloud-based network management and configuration platform for campus, branch, remote, and data center networks. There are various needs for automation and programmability like automating repetitive tasks, configuring multiple devices, monitoring, and more.

This workspace has a Postman collection for HPE Aruba Networking Central's REST APIs.

To make any API calls to Aruba Central in this collection, set **HPE Aruba Networking Central ENV** as the active environment & update **base_url** & **access_token** variables with valid values. Here is what these variables refer to:

- **Base URL -** Domain Base URL for HPE Aruba Networking Central API Gateway based on the geographical cluster where your account is registered. Please check the table below to see the Base URL corresponding to your HPE Aruba Networking Central account cluster:
    

| Region | API Gateway Base URL |
| --- | --- |
| US-1 | [https://app1-apigw.central.arubanetworks.com](https://app1-apigw.central.arubanetworks.com) |
| US-2 | [https://apigw-prod2.central.arubanetworks.com](https://apigw-prod2.central.arubanetworks.com) |
| US-East1 | [https://apigw-us-east-1.central.arubanetworks.com](https://apigw-us-east-1.central.arubanetworks.com) |
| US-West4 | [https://apigw-uswest4.central.arubanetworks.com](https://apigw-uswest4.central.arubanetworks.com) |
| EU-1 | [https://eu-apigw.central.arubanetworks.com](https://eu-apigw.central.arubanetworks.com) |
| EU-Central2 | [https://apigw-eucentral2.central.arubanetworks.com](https://apigw-eucentral2.central.arubanetworks.com) |
| EU-Central3 | [https://apigw-eucentral3.central.arubanetworks.com](https://apigw-eucentral3.central.arubanetworks.com) |
| Canada-1 | [https://apigw-ca.central.arubanetworks.com](https://apigw-ca.central.arubanetworks.com) |
| China-1 | [https://apigw.central.arubanetworks.com.cn](https://apigw.central.arubanetworks.com.cn) |
| APAC-1 | [https://api-ap.central.arubanetworks.com](https://api-ap.central.arubanetworks.com) |
| APAC-EAST1 | [https://apigw-apaceast.central.arubanetworks.com](https://apigw-apaceast.central.arubanetworks.com) |
| APAC-SOUTH1 | [https://apigw-apacsouth.central.arubanetworks.com](https://apigw-apacsouth.central.arubanetworks.com) |
| UAE-NORTH1 | [https://apigw-uaenorth1.central.arubanetworks.com](https://apigw-uaenorth1.central.arubanetworks.com) |

- **Access Token -** Access Token is required to securely make an API Request to HPE Aruba Networking Central API Gateway. You can obtain an access token from -
    
    - [HPE Aruba Networking Central Web UI](https://developer.arubanetworks.com/aruba-central/docs/api-gateway-obtaining-access-tokens#obtain-access-token-via-web-ui)
        
    - [OAuth APIs](https://developer.arubanetworks.com/aruba-central/docs/api-gateway-obtaining-access-tokens#obtain-access-token-via-web-ui) (For Non-SSO Users)
        - You can create access tokens using OAuth APIs from [Create Token collection folder](https://www.postman.com/hpe-aruba-networking/workspace/aruba-central/folder/30369652-6ca035f3-bab1-4864-8711-c9913471cc3c?ctx=documentation) in this collection.
            

For more details, please check out [HPE Aruba Networking Central's guides](https://developer.arubanetworks.com/aruba-central/docs/central-about) on [devHub](https://devhub.arubanetworks.com/home).

Site thresholds

query_params.description:
used as a page number when working with paginated results, with the first page being at offset 0 and last page at  Math.ceil(total_items/limit)-1. 

For example: Assuming you have a collection of 100 items, and you want to retrieve them in batches of 20 items per page. Here's how you can use limit and offset in your API request: 

Example 1: Retrieve the first page of items 
API Request: GET with limit=20&offset=0 
API Response: Returns the first 20 items in the collection.

Example 2: Retrieve the second page of items 
API Request: GET with limit=20&offset=1 
API Response: Returns the next 20 items in the collection, starting from item 21 to item 40. 

Example 3: Retrieve the sixth page of items 
API Request: GET with limit=20&offset=5 
API Response: Returns an empty response, as there are no items available from item 101 to item 120 in the collection.
specifies the maximum number of items per page. Default 100,  Max 100.
METERS or FEET
